aas_core.aas3_0.types.impl

Class Blob

  • java.lang.Object
    • aas_core.aas3_0.types.impl.Blob
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IBlob, IClass, IDataElement, IHasDataSpecification, IHasExtensions, IHasSemantics, IQualifiable, IReferable, ISubmodelElement

    public class Blob
extends Object
implements IBlob
    A Blob is a data element that represents a file that is contained with its source code in the value attribute.

      • getCategory

        public Optional<String> getCategory()
        Description copied from interface: IReferable
        The category is a value that gives further meta information w.r.t. to the class of the element. It affects the expected existence of attributes and the applicability of constraints.

        The category is not identical to the semantic definition (IHasSemantics) of an element. The category e.g. could denote that the element is a measurement value whereas the semantic definition of the element would denote that it is the measured temperature.

        Specified by:
        getCategory in interface IReferable

        public Optional<String> getIdShort()
        Description copied from interface: IReferable
        In case of identifiables this attribute is a short name of the element. In case of referable this ID is an identifying string of the element within its name space.

        In case the element is a property and the property has a semantic definition (IHasSemantics.getSemanticId()) conformant to IEC61360 the IReferable.getIdShort() is typically identical to the short name in English.

      • getContentType

        public String getContentType()
        Description copied from interface: IBlob
        Content type of the content of the Blob.

        The content type (MIME type) states which file extensions the file can have.

        Valid values are content types like e.g. application/json, application/xls, image/jpg.

        The allowed values are defined as in RFC2046.

        Specified by:
        getContentType in interface IBlob
